The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 13: The empowered committee of state finance ministers on VAT will continue to monitor and co-ordinate with states even after the introduction of the value-added tax (VAT) from next month across the country. ?The empowered committee has been registered as a society with state finance ministers as members,? VAT panel sources said today. The move is seen as a precursor to the process of converging the tax rates of states with the Cenvat rate of the Centre to arrive at a single national VAT.

 Mumbai, March 13: The National Commodity and Derivatives Exchange Ltd (NCDEX) plans to float indices on the lines of nifty soon and launch futures contract in energy. HDFC Bank is planning to pick up a 2-5 per cent stake in NCDEX.

 London, March 13: SBI Capital Markets will open more offices outside India. ?Besides the London office launched this week, the firm plans to open offices either in Hong Kong, Singapore or New York ? whichever comes first ? and one in Dubai,? MD and CEO Indrajit Gupta said.

 New Delhi, March 13: Hyundai Motor India today said exports would grow over 100 per cent this fiscal to about 85,000 units against 42,113 vehicles shipped abroad in 2003-04.

 New Delhi, March 13: The government is finalising the National Maritime Development Policy to ensure infrastructure development in ports and forge public-private partnership.




